  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study is to provide gait parameters as a new objective method to assess
      total knee arthroplasty outcome between patients with fixed- and mobile-bearing, using an
      ambulatory device with minimal sensor configuration.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
